The paper discusses the development of bibliometric publisher rankings, which involves analyzing research performance and impact. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), library and information science (cs.LIS), cybernetics (cs.CY), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, since the focus is on analyzing research impact, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.LIS, cs.CY, and cs.SI.
